<section class="sap-preflight">
  <h2>SAP-side preflight</h2>
  <p>Before any tool touches your SAP system, you need four things confirmed
  on the SAP side. Skipping these steps is the most common cause of extraction
  failures, performance incidents, and licensing surprises.</p>

  <ol class="sap-preflight-checklist">
    <li>
      <strong>License — confirm your extraction method is covered.</strong>
      <p>
        <a href="/articles/runtime-vs-full-use/">Runtime vs Full Use</a> is the
        first decision. ODP-based extraction (via
        <a href="/glossary/odp/">ODP</a>) is permitted under Runtime licenses.
        SLT replication requires a Full Use license. Verify with your SAP
        licensing contact before you design anything — not the day before
        go-live.
      </p>
      <p class="sap-preflight-note">
        <strong>SAP Note 3255746 (Feb 2024):</strong> Use of ODP RFC function
        modules by third-party tools is no longer permitted. If your tool uses
        ODP via RFC (ADF SAP CDC, Qlik, Fivetran ODP, etc.), verify your
        contract terms. Compliant alternatives are ODP via OData or SLT
        replication. Full note at
        <a href="https://support.sap.com/notes/3255746" target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">support.sap.com/notes/3255746</a>
        (SAP login required). [NEEDS_SAP_CITATION — verify current note version]
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Released CDS view — confirm the extraction-safe view exists.</strong>
      <p>
        Every table covered in this Academy has a SAP-released
        <a href="/glossary/cds-view/">CDS view</a> annotated for extraction.
        Open
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/SE80.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SE80</a>
        and search for the view name before you build anything. Confirm the
        annotation <code>@Analytics.dataExtract: true</code> is present. If
        the view is absent or the annotation is missing, stop — raw table
        extraction is not the solution.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Authorizations — grant the extraction user minimum permissions.</strong>
      <p>
        Your extraction user needs three authorization objects.
        Use
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_NETWEAVER_750/wm_netweaver_740_ehp1_html/ae58e3c3a8c54e6f9573f3b0ee75ea94.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SU01</a>
        to create a System-type (non-dialog) user, then use
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_NETWEAVER_750/wm_netweaver_740_ehp1_html/e5e83c2825c34a7896bdb97c0da65fb5.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PFCG</a>
        to assign a role containing:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>S_RFC</code> — allows RFC calls (set <code>RFC_TYPE=FUNC</code>)</li>
        <li><code>S_ODP_READ</code> — allows reading from ODP contexts
          (set <code>ODPSOURCE=ABAP_CDS</code> for CDS-based extraction)</li>
        <li><code>S_TABU_DIS</code> — table display access for the relevant
          authorization group</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For SLT-based extraction, your Basis team will also need authorization
        in
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/LTCO.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LTCO</a>
        and
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/LTRS.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LTRS</a>.
        [NEEDS_SAP_CITATION — confirm exact auth objects for LTCO/LTRS]
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <strong>Row-count context — understand data volumes before you run.</strong>
      <p>
        Use
        <a href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f69a8fb28ac48d89de2381c2f02a1e9/SE16N.html"
          target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SE16N</a>
        to count rows in the target table with your intended filter (company
        code, fiscal year, material type, etc.) before you start the
        extraction. This gives you:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>A baseline to reconcile against after the extract.</li>
        <li>A sense of whether your partition is safe to extract
          (&lt;&nbsp;100M rows is generally safe for ODP;
          larger partitions may need further splitting or SLT).</li>
        <li>Early warning if a filter is misconfigured
          (count returns billions — rethink the partition).</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p class="sap-preflight-footer">
    These four checks take 15–30 minutes on a first walkthrough, and under
    5 minutes once you know your system. They are the difference between a
    smooth extraction and a multi-day incident.
  </p>
</section>
